.TH DICTEE-SWITCH-BACKEND 1 "March 2026" "dictee 1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dictee-switch-backend \- switch ASR or translation backend for dictee
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee-switch-backend
.I command
.RI [ backend ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dictee-switch-backend
switches the active ASR or translation backend. For ASR, it updates
.I ~/.config/dictee.conf
and restarts the corresponding systemd user service. For translation, it only updates the configuration (no service restart needed).
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show the current ASR and translation backends.
.TP
.BI "asr " backend
Switch the ASR backend.
.I backend
is one of:
.BR parakeet ", " canary ", " vosk ", " whisper .
.TP
.BI "translate " backend
Switch the translation backend.
.I backend
is one of:
.BR google ", " bing ", " ollama ", " libretranslate .
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
dictee-switch-backend status
dictee-switch-backend asr canary
dictee-switch-backend translate ollama
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dictee.conf
Main configuration file (shell-sourceable key=value format).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dictee (1),
.BR dictee-setup (1),
.BR dictee-tray (1)
